abstract: Pete Buttigieg, the 37-year-old Democratic mayor of South Bend, Ind., has gained surprising early visibility in the 2020 presidential race. Also known as “Mayor Pete,” he is vying to become the first openly gay president.

abstract: It’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the stories you might have missed.
snippet: It’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the stories you might have missed.
lead_paragraph: From a Department of Homeland Security shake-up to the arrest of Julian Assange, it’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the biggest stories you might have missed (and some links if you’d like to read further).
headline_main: On Politics: The Biggest Stories of the Week

abstract: The attack amplified a controversy that has been a focus of conservative news outlets, which have sought to elevate Ms. Omar, a Muslim lawmaker, as a political target.
snippet: The attack amplified a controversy that has been a focus of conservative news outlets, which have sought to elevate Ms. Omar, a Muslim lawmaker, as a political target.
lead_paragraph: President Trump on Friday targeted Representative Ilhan Omar for remarks she made during a speech on civil rights and Muslims in America with a graphic video featuring the burning World Trade Center towers and other images from Sept. 11, 2001, that he tweeted to millions of his followers.

abstract: Republicans are poll-testing ways to portray Democrats as too extreme on issues like health care, abortion and the environment, and Democrats worry that the messaging is working.
snippet: Republicans are poll-testing ways to portray Democrats as too extreme on issues like health care, abortion and the environment, and Democrats worry that the messaging is working.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican leaders are sharpening and poll-testing lines of attack that portray Democratic policies on health care, the environment and abortion as far outside the norm, in hopes of arming President Trump with hyperbolic sound bites — some of them false — asserting that Democrats would cause long waits for doctors or make killing babies after birth legal.

headline_main: With Polls and Private Meetings, Republicans Craft Blunt Messaging to Paint Democrats as Extreme
headline_print_headline: G.O.P. Hones Blunt, Misleading Attacks on the Democrats

abstract: The progressive leaders Pete Buttigieg and Stacey Abrams are confronting the hypocrisy of the religious right.
snippet: The progressive leaders Pete Buttigieg and Stacey Abrams are confronting the hypocrisy of the religious right.
lead_paragraph: We know that slaveholders in the American South used Scripture to justify keeping their fellow humans in bondage. They could find no words from Christ on this, for there are no words from him. Just a line in the New Testament from mere mortals presuming to speak for him.

abstract: Candidates should tell us what they actually love to read, and there shouldn’t be any wrong answers.
snippet: Candidates should tell us what they actually love to read, and there shouldn’t be any wrong answers.
lead_paragraph: One of my fondest memories of motherhood is of when my younger daughter, Phoebe, learned to read. It was bedtime, and her sister, her stepfather and I were settled in bed with our books. I kissed Phoebe good night and left the light on, and as I walked down the hall I heard her announce, “I am part of the reading family now!” (I felt good about my parenting, in a way I hadn’t since the incident, a few weeks previously, when, on our way to a doctor’s appointment, my other kid looked up at me with a sunny smile and announced, “Guess what I am not wearing today!”)

abstract: The poll, conducted by Monmouth University, also indicated that support for Mayor Pete Buttigieg is on the rise.
snippet: The poll, conducted by Monmouth University, also indicated that support for Mayor Pete Buttigieg is on the rise.
lead_paragraph: Despite a turbulent week in which he was accused by several women of inappropriate physical contact, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. remains popular among Iowa Democrats and leads a new poll that also indicates Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., is on the rise.
